This paper is primarily focused on analyzing and understanding Internet traffic, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the importance of isolated links and leaf nodes in Internet traffic, which could be relevant to the field of computer security (cs.CR) and social networks (cs.SI). The use of large-scale data analysis and modeling techniques could also be relevant to the fields of data science (cs.DS) and computer engineering (cs.CE).
